GLOBAL
Road conditions: posted at city gates and inn boards; update daily; fresh
reports of raider activity sell well; stale reports get people killed
Survival basics: water sources in the eastern desert are the Oasis-Pyramid
Corridor's wells; carry three days' supply minimum; sandstorms move fast
Saltglass Reach: the overland desert corridor from the pyramid settlements
to Mafdet; sand-pirate raids are frequent; Sand-Sea Carters' Guild patrols
but cannot cover the full route; travel in groups
~

MIDGAARD
Great Northern Forest lies between Midgaard and the Kowloon delta; road
wardens track Ashfang warband and Rootbound cult movements; current
intelligence posted at the north gate
Lantern Road is the formalized trade artery through the forest; disruptions
ripple through to Kiess within days
Cinderteeth Mountains: far northwest; volcanic; active seismic zones;
eruptions produce toxic mineral particulate; the Ashborn are immune
Temple of the Resounding Heart runs a seismological watch; eruption alerts
reach the city via signal relay
Abandoned Spirebound Conclave sanctum rumored somewhere in the Cinderteeth;
location disputed; what remains inside is unknown and possibly still active
~

KOWLOON
Great Northern Forest lies south between Kowloon and Midgaard; the Lantern
Road is the primary land route; warband activity can cut it without warning
Jhen River provides the alternate route; delta flooding in wet season makes
overland travel through the forest preferable despite the risks
~

KIESS
Forest of Confusion lies north of the city; formed from a failed druidic
quarantine merged with an ancient forest intelligence (the Verdant Depths)
Mist-fever: psychoactive disorientation with prolonged mist exposure; not
natural weather; onset sudden; symptoms include false memories and
inability to determine direction
Kiess Wall Command maintains rope-line corridors through the southern verge;
do not enter without a guide or a rope-line
Withered Depths deeper in: blight from Conclave crystal experiments in root
systems; plant-based creatures in blighted zones are aggressive; corrupted
organic matter propagates on contact
Verdant Depths at the forest core: distributed living intelligence; Heartwood
Guardians protect the core; no formal contact with city governance
~

MAFDET
Eastern Desert: Oasis-Pyramid Corridor connects inland pyramid sites to the
coast; rival excavation camps compete for site access
Ancient tombs throughout; trap mechanisms still function; guardian constructs
do not distinguish excavators from grave robbers
Scorching Sands: extreme heat zones; travel at night; daytime temperatures
kill unprotected travelers within hours
Sand pirates follow caravan schedules and have informants in departure cities
~
